1) What is REST ?
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Rest stands for representational state transfer.

2) What is Http? 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Http stands for hyper text tranfer protocol.

3) RESTFul web services ?
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Restful webs service is developed by roy fielding , the main purpose of Restful web service is application to application interaction.
suppose your have application A, B and C written those in java , php and dotnet.
so they can interact with each other or communicate with each other with help of REST protocol.

4) Methods of REST API
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I) POST - post we have to create a new resource.


for eg - 

@PostMapping("/save")
public ResponseEntity<Employee> saveEmployee(@RequestBody Employee employee){

}

II)GET - get used to get the resource

@GetMapping("/find/{id}")
public Employee getEmployee(@pathvariable long empId){

}

III) Put - put basically we have to update the resource

@PutMapping("/update")
public ResponseEntity<Employee> updateEmployee(@RequestBody Employee employee){

}

IV) Patch - patch we have for partial update the resource.

@PatchMapping("/partialUpdate)
public ResponseEntity<Employee> partialUpdateEmployeeDetails(@RequestBody Employee employee){

}

V) Delete - delete the resource.

@DeleteMapping("/delete/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<String> delete(@PathVaribale long empId){

}

5) What is the difference between SOAP VS REST ?

SOAP - i) soap stands for simple object access protocol.
       ii) it mainly used for xml data exchange.
       iii) soap is a protocol.
       iv) soap is difficult to implement.

REST - i) rest stands for representational state transfer.
       ii) rest used for json data transfer.
       iii) Rest is architectural approch.
       iv) Rest is easy to implement.


6) Status code
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
200 - Ok 
201 - Created
400 - Method Not found
404 - bad request
500 - internal server error
